gomodel:SYNGO_978  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Data show quantitative immunogold labelling of postsynaptic structures in cortex (Figure 3) and hippocampus (Figure 4). Although clearly postsynaptic with accumulation at dendrites widespread receptor labelling is not juxtaposed to cholinergic release sites. This positioned to act as a postsynaptic sensor of volume transmission. Immunoreactivity controlled for specificity on knock out tissue.\n\n17/8/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Material and methods Adult C57Bl/6 mice were used...." ;
